        "created_at": "2024-10-31T02:15:41.066Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi folks, I have noticed that after a Signal restart from an update, the Windows desktop client has moved window size and/or position so I canâ€™t see the last message; the window hangs off the bottom of my screen.</p>\n<p>So I started Microsoft Spy++ which is a Visual Studio tool that can interrogate windows information, and grabbed the size and position after closing and starting the client (i.e. without an update).</p>\n<p>Each restart, the window will migrate 1 pixel left and up, and the width and height will increase by 5 pixels.</p>\n<p>I am running <strong>7.31.0 production</strong>.<br>\n<img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/6/0/6056732e036e47c232f69452738d1ab4e9ff8101.png\" alt=\"InitialSize\" data-base62-sha1=\"dKf3qr2lgF3glL97xacqWlzblgl\" width=\"397\" height=\"202\"><br>\n<img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/1/a/1abf8f254a5681786899d2e4a2e60a464c037255.png\" alt=\"Restart1\" data-base62-sha1=\"3OCPkeEXbHF8EV91Jdb95XyQYap\" width=\"397\" height=\"201\"><br>\n<img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/7/9/7952c3193e3624bfc381a788fd8bd1d38a940ae5.png\" alt=\"Restart2\" data-base62-sha1=\"hjh5Dtp76LHRU5rehlvJgPJ7DmZ\" width=\"394\" height=\"198\"></p>",
